**Segments**

The Healthcare Business Process Outsourcing (BPO) market can be segmented based on services, provider, payer, and pharmaceutical. In terms of services, the market can be further categorized into front-office services, middle-office services, and back-office services. Front-office services include customer relationship management, while middle-office services encompass revenue cycle management and claims management. Back-office services involve HR management and finance and accounting services. By provider, the market can be divided into healthcare payer BPO and healthcare provider BPO. Healthcare payer BPO includes services related to insurance processing, while healthcare provider BPO involves services such as patient enrollment and care management. Additionally, the pharmaceutical segment within healthcare BPO includes research and development services, sales and marketing services, and supply chain management.

